#+title: Internet Connections
* Internet Access Technologies
You have many options to choose from when connecting to the internet.

Home networks, remote workers and small offices typically require an ISP to access the internet. The ISP offers for example broadband cable, broadband digital subscriber line (DSL), wireless WANs, and mobile services.

Larger oranizations usually require access to the internet as well as access to other corprate sites. SPs offer business-class interconnections. These include business DSL, leased lines or Metro Ethernet.
